      "fix": "Change to `const offset = (page - 1) * pageSize;`",
      "time_to_fix": "< 1 minute",
      "acceptance_criteria_affected": "API contract: pages are 1-indexed per documentation. Current code is 0-indexed."
    },
    {
      "title": "No input validation allows negative offset, zero/negative pageSize",
      "risk": "page=0 or negative values produce nonsensical queries. pageSize=0 returns nothing. Negative pageSize may throw a database error or return all rows depending on the driver. A very large pageSize (e.g. 1000000) dumps the entire table.",
      "severity": "High",
      "location": "getOrderHistory, function parameters",
      "reproduction": "Call getOrderHistory('cust_1', -1, 10) → offset = -10, database behavior is undefined. Call getOrderHistory('cust_1', 1, 0) → LIMIT 0, returns empty. Call getOrderHistory('cust_1', 1, 999999) → returns unbounded rows, potential OOM or slow response.",
      "fix": "Add guards: `if (page < 1) throw new Error('page must be >= 1'); if (pageSize < 1 || pageSize > 100) throw new Error('pageSize must be between 1 and 100');`",
      "time_to_fix": "5 minutes",
      "acceptance_criteria_affected": "API robustness — invalid inputs should return 400, not silently produce wrong results or crash."
    }
